<p>Me too.  I&#8217;ve found I sometimes confuse people by the way I frequently get nervous, inarticulate, or even tongue-tied in in-person interactions.  I tend to come across very strongly and assertively online, where I have time to get my words in order, where the words come out much more easily and smoothly than they have to when I&#8217;m attempting to vocalise.  Whereas if I have the slightest bit of anxiousness in person, pfft.  I lose most of that in just inability to find language.</p>
<p>I actually, when working through complicated emotional stuff with my liege, tend to write him emails and then go sit with him on the couch while he reads them on his laptop.  Because it&#8217;s orders of magnitude easier than talking, even in a relationship so intimate and trust-based.</p>
